## Language Policy

- AI responses, code comments, and commit messages follow the configured project language policy.

## Source Ownership

- Read `.autopus/project/workspace.md` first when present. It defines root and nested-repo boundaries, tracking policy, generated/runtime paths, canonical source locations, and QA target routing such as `auto qa init --project-dir <repo>`.
- Resolve a SPEC from `.autopus/specs/{SPEC-ID}/spec.md`, then recursive module roots excluding generated/dependency directories. Stop on zero or duplicate matches.

## Subagent Delegation

- Preserve the configured subagent-first execution contract. `--auto` authorizes the pipeline and `--solo` explicitly chooses one session.
- If runtime policy prevents implicit delegation, report that constraint and request opt-in or `--solo`; never silently downgrade.

## Review Convergence

- Separate initial finding discovery from verification. Retry only open findings against the updated diff and retain configured limits.

## Generated Surface Safety

- Never directly edit `.claude/**`, `.codex/**`, `.gemini/**`, `.opencode/**`, or `.autopus/plugins/**` generated/runtime surfaces.
- Modify the canonical ADK template/source, regenerate, and keep generated/runtime drift out of commits.

